or six of them are women.

00:09:02.310 --> 00:09:05.960 align:middle line:10%
So I've learned, I was real
heavy on the masculine.

00:09:05.960 --> 00:09:09.290 align:middle line:10%
And I really wasn't utilizing
the feminine part of me.

00:09:09.290 --> 00:09:17.120 align:middle line:10%
And they awakened that
through my psychologist,

00:09:17.120 --> 00:09:19.700 align:middle line:10%
through my energy
and body workers,

00:09:19.700 --> 00:09:23.180 align:middle line:10%
through others that
mentored me, with me.

00:09:23.180 --> 00:09:25.950 align:middle line:90%
So I want to credit that first.

00:09:25.950 --> 00:09:29.120 align:middle line:84%
Now, how is that
accepted by other men?

00:09:29.120 --> 00:09:31.095 align:middle line:84%
Or how has that
affected other men?

00:09:31.095 --> 00:09:31.970 align:middle line:90%
Is that the question?

00:09:31.970 --> 00:09:33.180 align:middle line:90%
>> It is the question.

00:09:33.180 --> 00:09:34.970 align:middle line:84%
Because you're such
a great example.

00:09:34.970 --> 00:09:39.060 align:middle line:84%
And I think men will have a
hard time looking at a woman

00:09:39.060 --> 00:09:39.860 align:middle line:90%
